Leichardt County was named in honour of the Prussian naturalist and explorer Friedrich Wilhelm Ludwig Leichhart (1813-1848).

Leichardt County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is located south of the Namoi River and includes land on both sides of the Castlereagh River , including Coonamble .
